column1: 203030;instagram;2019-02-06 12:08:24;FALSE;"♥️♠️♥️♠️vic mignogna has been fired by rooster teeth. will not voice qrow in vol. 7.
i should be sleeping right now but this was bothering me. imo even if vic mignogna has done everything he has been accused of
column2: this is not an appropriate way of handling the situation. believe all victims but that doesn't mean throw sanity out the window. it means listen to accusations
column4: and investigate. firing someone on accusations alone is ridiculous. what stops me from making an accusation against someone i don't like and getting them fired if this is how we do things now?? public figures draw so much more attention and anyone can say anything and it will get some traction on the internet 100% of the time. this kind of kneejerk reaction is gonna blow up one day with a false accusation and it's gonna make things harder for real victims. also
column6: rts statement was weak and reeks of corporate legal team and i'm saying this all as someone who is pretty positive vic did do some inappropriate stuff and may be guilty of everything he's accused
column7: it's still just not the way things should be done.

column1: as for the situation with qrow... i dunno what's gonna happen and i'm really worried. vic had a really distinctive voice and i'm worried that after a season where qrow was already the most poorly written and unlikable he's ever been rt are gonna recast him and try to bury it by killing him in a rush job worse than adam. the way some ppl (not me) responded to adam's death (anger
column2: dropping show) will be me if they sweep qrow under the rug with a shitty death because of an awkward voice change due to bad internet politics. i really hope they don't try to mimic vic and let someone do their own thing with the voice and let us get used to it over a few volumes and give qrow a proper chance.

column1: 203068;instagram;2019-02-06 13:20:01;TRUE;;"you are the expert on your body and your experiences! keep reading for some very important wisdom from @whole_embodied_therapist. ❤️
you are the expert on your body
column2: your experience & your story.  we know when an event is acknowledged as trauma
column3: it is hugely protective against the development of trauma symptoms.  conversely
column4: when one’s experience is not acknowledged
column7: is far more difficult for the body and brain to heal. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

column1: to all who’ve experienced trauma- it’s real.  it matters.  i believe you and your experience. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
to those who love or care for someone whose experienced trauma
column2: be present and listen when asked.  the best thing you can do is let someone speak if and when they are ready.  don’t interrogate
column3: don’t try to fix or try to ease the pain (i know that’s hard)...just be there and when asked
column4: just listen and expressed you believe their experience and you’re with them. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

column1: healing from trauma isn’t linear.  it looks different for everyone.  your story and your journey are your own- and if you need support
column2: i hope you’ll reach out. you’re not alone. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

column1: february is the month of love. and at the age of 23
column3: i genuinely don’t think i know what love really is. i suppose it’s different for all of us. but i’ve decided to share with you a selection of books that have taught me something about my relationship with love.

column1: it ends with us by colleen hoover
column3: a woman who has a whirlwind romance with a lovely man who in the space of 15 seconds becomes abusive and obsessive. the story shows her relationship with the loves of her life; her husband
column6: her friends and how that has influenced her concept of love. its a genuinely heart wrenching story because you wish that her husband wasn’t like this. he is portrayed as such a wonderful “ideal” partner. but this juxtaposition shows how many of our favourite romantic hero’s are abusive characters. they’re all portrayed as these fantastic
column7: wonderful soul mates when in reality they are guilty of gas lighting

column2: why do we forgive and forget it? from instances in reality to those of fiction
column3: we are so ready and able to forget the despicable behaviour of abusers. why?

column1: it ends with us taught me the difference between love and obsession. how genuine love is never supposed to hurt or bruise or cut.
it also taught me the complexities of abuse. how it’s not always physical
column2: how it is can be mental
column3: and how both of these forms of abuse can be equally as traumatic.

column1: want a love story that will make you question your concept of love? read some hoover.

column1: 203180;instagram;2019-02-06 14:59:03;FALSE;"チャン・グンソク主演作ながら…😅💦 6日、北海道・札幌市内のホテルで「ゆうばり国際ファンタスティック映画祭2019」のラインナップ発表会見が行われ、本映画祭の大賞となるファンタスティック・オフシアター・コンペティション部門の審査委員長を『凶悪』『孤狼の血』などで知られる北海道出身のヒットメーカー、白石和彌監督が務めることが明らかになった。 　同部門の審査員はほかに、韓国・プチョン国際ファンタスティック映画祭プログラマーを務めるモ・ウニョン、映画評論家のマーク・シリング、『南瓜とマヨネーズ』『素敵なダイナマイトスキャンダル』などの冨永昌敬監督、「太陽にほえろ！」シリーズなどに出演していた女優の長谷直美が務める。 　一方、短編作品のコンペ部門であるインターナショナル・ショートフィルム・コンペティション部門の審査委員長は、映画監督の久保直樹が担う。ほか審査員は『モリのいる場所』などの沖田修一監督と『0.5ミリ』などの安藤桃子監督。

クロージング作品は『レゴ(r)ムービー2』！ - (c) 2019 warner bros. entertaiment inc. 　オープニングを飾る招待作品はチャン・グンソクの主演作ながら、ベルリン映画祭でワールドプレミアされて以来、「#metoo」運動を受けてお蔵入りしていた『人間、空間、時間、そして人間（仮題）』。クロージング作品は玩具lego(r)をテーマにした『lego(r)ムービー』の続編『レゴ(r)ムービー2』で、ゾンビパニックに直面した高校生たちを歌とダンスを交えて描くミュージカル映画『アナと世界の終わり』も招待作品として上映される。";;en;;;;;;0;;miyabi.j;miyabi;;0;False;7;0;0;43;https://instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net/vp/2d6f34e1dc831369e6cf7dbc770a1497/5D28A3C7/t51.2885-15/e35/50722788_121060108957294_6852719658882125740_n.jpg?_nc_ht=instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net;0;FALSE;FALSE;FALSE;english;"チャン・グンソク主演作ながら…😅💦 6日、北海道・札幌市内のホテルで「ゆうばり国際ファンタスティック映画祭2019」のラインナップ発表会見が行われ、本映画祭の大賞となるファンタスティック・オフシアター・コンペティション部門の審査委員長を『凶悪』『孤狼の血』などで知られる北海道出身のヒットメーカー、白石和彌監督が務めることが明らかになった。 　同部門の審査員はほかに、韓国・プチョン国際ファンタスティック映画祭プログラマーを務めるモ・ウニョン、映画評論家のマーク・シリング、『南瓜とマヨネーズ』『素敵なダイナマイトスキャンダル』などの冨永昌敬監督、「太陽にほえろ！」シリーズなどに出演していた女優の長谷直美が務める。 　一方、短編作品のコンペ部門であるインターナショナル・ショートフィルム・コンペティション部門の審査委員長は、映画監督の久保直樹が担う。ほか審査員は『モリのいる場所』などの沖田修一監督と『0.5ミリ』などの安藤桃子監督。

column3: and behaviors of industry leaders have completely changed my perception of what i thought i knew about the film industry.

column1: i knew the industry was a challenging field. i knew it was more difficult for women. however
column2: i now understand on a deeper level what those challenges are. the night i saw this film
column3: i couldn’t sleep at all. all i kept thinking was what am i going to do if i am not enough?

column3: i didn’t let this cloud my perception of what was really happening. i’m not one to get starstruck and i think this helps me always look at the bigger picture. i chose not to let the red carpet fool me. i am very grateful to sbiff. it has shown me the ugly realities of my dream and has challenged my passion for film. without this experience

column1: 203229;instagram;2019-02-06 15:50:51;FALSE;i cannot take it anymore. today has to be the last day i will cry in this bathroom here at my shop @thepaintedsiren. i am so scared of how this will go. i am going to risk losing it all to stand up for myself because i am done. everything i've sacrificed and worked so hard for.. my whole business and livelihood may be taken away from me if i persue this legal action. i am trying to be strong and think of dr. ford blassey and even tho i am not attempting to save a whole country
column2: maybe i can save myself. i have no choice anymore. i cannot fight for everyone but not for myself anymore. i know it is me who they will try and destroy but i've been through worse and somehow i have to believe that i will get through this too. i made a list of all the things my landlord has done
column3: its been 12 years.... i called the bar association for my county
column4: they weren't open yet of course but it made me feel like i was doing it and i will call again when they are. i cannot move forward and finish healing if this is my life

column1: 203284;instagram;2019-02-06 16:34:48;FALSE;"#metoo #domesticviolence messiah @louisfarrakhan teaches ""there are things in our lives that have been done to us. from the time we were babies
column2: a word from a mother that wasn't thinking; a father that didn't care; a teacher that was off the mark who

column1: and these commands are in your head

column2: who has been ‪raped‬ by a father
column5: by a relative: college doesn't free you; church doesn't free you from that pain. it gives you an emotional escape. but to relieve you
column6: and give you a chance to live … see
column7: the scientologists call this process ‪auditing ‬. but we who are muslims
column9: we don't use the term engrams. in theology
column10: we call it the exorcising of demons.

column3: they just ask you to go back.

column1: every one of us has a file in our head
column2: and the auditor will take you back to a moment of pain  which is something that people did to you
column3: not so much what you did to others.

column1: when you look at our behavior

column4: making threats or taking advantage of victims not able to give consent.” in addressing this subject we need to look at the nonconsensual sexual activities between adults that occur in unequal relationships where one person exercises power and authority over the other. in the case of priests and bishops
column5: they hold the power of position over nuns and members of their church community that makes true equality impossible. any sexual relationships they might have - even if the adult partner believes she or he is offering consent - is tainted by this unequal balance of power.

column1: it is easy for priests and bishops who exhibit the traits of “sexual manipulators” to find spiritually vulnerable women and men who trust their religious leaders to have their best interests at heart. the truth is
column2: these men have their own interests at heart and that includes being satisfied sexually and emotionally by the adulation of others. what makes them even more dangerous is that they have often persuaded themselves to believe they are doing what is best for the women and men who satisfy them sexually. they can even confidently claim that they are helping to strengthen their sexual partner’s spiritual relationship with god by teaching them how to “love.” ...................so when i read this headline in the today’s newspapers
column3: i am reminded of the priest i knew decades ago who was a master manipulator of nuns
column5: single and divorced women who came to him for spiritual direction. after having seen how the catholic church protected this man and so many others from being publicly censored or privately stopped
column6: i have little confidence that the vatican will now have the will or intention to stop the sexual abuse of nuns. but that does not mean these women should remain silent. oh no! they must set up such a clamor for justice that the church cannot ignore them!  #metoo #sexualabuseofnuns";;en;#MeToo

column1: 🔸being a girl has always been tough. we face decisions and realities that men just don’t face. traumatic events in our lives shape us into the women we become. we are in a point of human history where it is time for us as women to speak up and say enough is enough. all women must unite! no matter your religion
column4: being a woman binds us all in sisterhood. every time a woman stands up for herself
column5: she stands up for all women!

column1: 203549;instagram;2019-02-06 21:04:28;FALSE;"tw: rape/sexual assault. “so i was friends with this man since jr high. 2008 we began dating. then one night he took me to meet his mom and when we arrived at her home it was pitch black. she was asleep. his 3 year old daughter was asleep in the room he took me in. he began to kiss me and his daughter woke up. he then got on top of me and when i said stop stop it was like he didn’t even hear me. he ignored me.

i went totally paralyzed and couldn’t believe this was happening. he wasn’t some scary man hiding in the bushes that i didn’t know. he was a friend. a familiar face. someone i had known for 7 years. months went by and i finally reported it. but was told i had no physical evidence.
when i tried talking to him about it he said “you’re just mad because i dumped you.”
i’m just now getting the mental help i need to overcome what he did. i blamed myself for years. maybe it wasn’t rape
column2: maybe i just felt disgusting because i’m not the promiscuous type?? maybe it was my fault because i put myself in that situation?? no. it was rape. he raped me. he sexually assaulted me. in front of his child.” - @frenchfriesandfairytales

column1: 203625;instagram;2019-02-06 23:31:17;FALSE;"i cannot reveal the “chosen” photo yet but my friend and artist @bumblegurl took this photo of me during our shoot and i’ve decided to use it for my professional photos. it’s meaningful to me.
i was chosen to be involved in her @survivor.project and she took one really fierce phot of my that i cannot wait to unveil
column2: when her series is ready. i love this photo too. but the other one really is something else. fierce.

column1: being involved in that project was so cathartic for me and really has been a big part of my healing. a lot of people don’t know that i’m a sexual assault survivor because i’ve never felt comfortable sharing it
column2: and haven’t always recognized the reality of it. i’ve also been in the receiving end of sexual harassment in the workplace and in my support/recovery group. i’ve kept a lot of this hidden because of shame

column1: the last couple years has been heavy; as i’ve been inundated with stories of sexual assault and abuse. but i can say that today
column2: i am working toward freedom from it and looking at how it has adversely affected my relationships over the years. trying to find ways to change and rewire my brain.
theresa. and thank you to all the survivors who’ve spoken out publicly. #metoo #survivor #nomoreshame #freedom #recovery #lettinggo";;en;#metoo

column1: 203628;instagram;2019-02-06 23:32:03;FALSE;"chic@s! no tengo idea cómo se sienten
column2: me gustaría que me cuenten. yo me siento esperanzada
column3: liberada y acompañada. lo de las últimas horas para nosotras es histórico. estamos hablando
column5: de romper el silencio ( gracias a la chica tan valiente y admirable que inició esto) y por otra
column6: de desafiar las estructuras de poder opresoras que han tratado de callarnos tanto tiempo.  hemos tenido mucho miedo y por nuestras mentes han pasado miles de veces razones de peso para no denunciar

column8: por todas las personas que pueden poner en tela de juicio nuestro testimonio
column9: por todos los que nos quieren responsabilizar
column10: por la posibilidad de que conocidos y seres queridos nos señalen
column11: por abrir heridas que nos ha costado muchísimo sanar. pero qué liberador es sentir que se comienzan a abrir espacios para denunciar y acuerparnos
column12: que hermoso es sentir que nos tenemos unas a otras en esto.

column1: 203800;instagram;2019-02-07 04:08:00;FALSE;"behind these eyes there is a story yet to be told. a past that haunts me even to this day. a deep scar that grew from infancy and kept growing deeper through the years. something that has affected every part of my life leading to posttraumatic stress disorder and paralysing nightmares. i have made it my mission in life to get justice. this person has been working with children for the last 20 years even after i finally was brave enough to tell my supportive parents and the police my story when i was 9 and still to this day continues in a job surrounded by children. i have been working on this case for years now and it saddens me that even though the police have received so much information of other victims and withnesses
column2: they still do nothing. i can no longer carry this weight on my shoulders alone. it is time for to speak out - and not suffer in silence!  i encourage anyone who has been affected by sexual abuse to speak out and go to the police no matter how ""small"" of an incident. only then can we have justice
column3: prevent lives to be ruined and finally be set free. behind this smile there is a sad story but i am a fighter and i know you are too. #metoo #metoomovement #childabusesurvivor suicideprevention #ptsdawareness #canaryislands #teacher #kripos #norskskolegrandcanaria #theinviciblescars #protectchildrenofthefuture #colegionoruego #grancan

column1: 203808;instagram;2019-02-07 04:11:12;FALSE;"in 15 days our life will embark on a new journey. we will walk a path that is unknown. i start a 13 week training to run a senior living community. many of you know i’m very passionate about working with the senior population. enhancing their quality of life in their last years is not only fun but very rewarding. we don’t know where our final move will be but the first stop on our journey is oregon.
i will continue to educate others on my other passion
column2: living a chemical free life and using oils and oil infused products to enhance our quality of life
column3: so that we can live our best life now and live a life above the wellness line. sickness has become the norm and we need to change that in society. we can no longer live the way that we have been living
column4: we must make a change! living above the wellness line is not hard
column5: it’s a choice. take charge of your health and wellness and do what you think is best for your family and friends
column6: don’t let anybody tell you what they think is best for you. you be your best advocate. preventative healthcare is the best type of healthcare. sick care is not healthcare.

column1: 203860;instagram;2019-02-07 05:35:23;FALSE;"ta för i helvete  allt annat än ett ja för ett nej!
det finns ett ord för detta som heter samtycke.
har jag inte fått samtycke av en annan människa så får jag inte ha sex med hen.
idagarna är det fyra år sen min vän @smurvlan blev utsatt för ett vidrigt sexualbrott av flera gärningsmän.
hon finner ändå kraft  att berätta öppet om händelsen.
tydligen så kan inte en kvinna ens kunna gå ensam till sin hytt.
detta är en händelse som hon aldrig kan förskjuta/glömma.
djupa sår som alltid kommer att kännas.

tänk på vad vi skapar hos brottsoffren. bara för att vi inte kan hålla kuken i styr. glömmer vi alla kvinnor vi älskar i våran närhet? vill vi att dem ska bli utsatta av några fyllon på en finnlandfärja?
@smurvlan du  hjälper många att våga anmäla och att prata om händelserna. tack ♀

column1: 203877;instagram;2019-02-07 06:00:16;FALSE;"what does girl director mean to me? 🤔
when i first created this iconic brand i was in a very low state of my life...
i was working in the television industry while it was still very much a boys club. there was constant set backs
column2: mistreatment and intimidation. no #metoo campaign to help me stand up for myself...

column1: the rachel i knew became worthless. the amazingly talented and driven rachel dunn was in fact
column2: invisible…. no matter what she did or didn’t do
column3: and no matter what others did to her – no one noticed.

column1: it was around this time i created girl director... she was a figure that represented everything i wanted to be 😍

column2: strong and not afraid to stick it to the man!

column1: she was also a figure that i could hide behind if i wanted to. although through a lot of hard work and self love the girl director brand has definitely evolved 🙌

column2: i represent the brand because i know there is no point hiding anymore.

column1: now i am able to help women every where to get through the past and see what is possible in the future. i help them shine
column2: stand out and best of all

column1: i am so grateful for what i have achieved and what i am able to do everyday. there is no stopping me now... just you watch! girl director is in full force now and there will be big changes in the near future!!!

column2: i want to hear your story because i know you have one. and i know it is worth telling!

column1: you are worth it! get in touch now! 🎬🎬

column1: today is my birthday.  i am officially middle aged!! that is not a bad thing!! it is a blessing. it means i may have witnessed some things and have an opinion that is worth hearing. .
i do not care what religion you follow.
what belief system brain washed you to become the person you are today.
what i care about is your intention.
1. do you want the world to be a better place.
2. do you understand that change starts with you and we as humans all have rights.
3. are you willing to be real and raw and honest and use your voice to help make the world just a bit calmer and better?
i hope you say yes to these simple questions.
if you don’t. i am sorry for you. i wish you well and i hope you find something to bring you to a place of acceptance and love. .
i am blessed to have been born in middle america and able to say these words without prosecution.
yet... as a women it still brought pause. but fuck it.  i am me. #firstlisten #reactless #listenmorespeakless #power

column1: super excited and skipping about while announcing the launch of 'ab aur nahin' -a side project of the @digitalrightsfoundation and essentially a directory of pro bono lawyers willing to give back to society by providing legal counsel and representation to victims of sexual harassment and abuse.

this is a project quite close at heart to drf's executive director @nighatdad and came about as an organically conceived brainchild of the team at large after receiving multiple queries regarding the addressal of cases of harassment
column2: though she remains the driving force behind it.

column3: you don't know who might benefit from this information. the prevalence of such incidences may seem to be on the rise but i genuinely believe that it is the courage brought about by the women of today and the support provided by their loved ones
column4: well-wishers and a larger community who won't stand for tolerating such behavior anymore
column5: that has increased the visibility of harassment and abuse. it has always existed
column6: insidiously and cripplingly pervasive in it's nature.

column1: does the irony suggest ""meaning to erase the rumor's fire""? 2018年5月26日、羽生はzhenyaとの間に立てられていた「奇妙な噂」を完全に否定した。
